    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Representation of an object, person, or structure in such a way that its most essential features are all seen in one view without regard to perspective or a single point of view. For visual works containing subjects depicting sequential episodes in one scene, use "continuous narration."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000032431/Ehresmann, Pocket Dictionary of Art Terms (1979)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Representación de un objeto, persona o estructura de tal manera que los elementos más esenciales son todos vistos en una sola visión sin tomar en cuenta la perspectiva o un solo punto de vista.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een object, persoon of structuur afgebeeld op een zodanige manier dat de meest belangrijke aspecten er van in één oogopslag worden gezien, zonder rekening met perspectief of een  enkelvoudig gezichtspunt te houden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種表現物件、人、結構的方式，將各種最主要的特色同時呈現在眼前，而不在乎透視法或單一視點。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
